(This is a response to this Sam Altman?s blog post . Sam Altman is not the bad guy. History) Tj
T*
(comes from two places, great men and causes and forces. We have way too little of the former) Tj
T*
(and way too much of the latter right now. I hear that in America people fear the government) Tj
T*
(taking away their freedom, and in China people fear the lack of government taking away their) Tj
T*
(freedom. Maybe it?s just because I have been living in Asia, but I don?t fear Sam or Elon or) Tj
T*
(Dario at all. I fear the Molochian tragedy of the commons. The small decisions made by millions) Tj
T*
(every day that make the world slightly worse for their fellow man, like adding a dark pattern) Tj
T*
(to a website, lobbying to siphon a few more tax dollars, posting an advertisement that uses) Tj
T*
(fear to sell, or enabling the tip screen in a coffee shop. I don?t fear ?great men,? I fear) Tj
T*
(that there?s no one coordinated enough to prevent this. Technology does not contain a destiny.) Tj
T*
(If you haven?t read Manna , now is a good time to. The choices we as a society make determine) Tj
T*
(our future. The blog post is far too trusting of the democratic worldview. I know it doesn?t) Tj
T*
(say UBI, but I hope you understand UBI is not a real solution, UBI is an extremel...) Tj
